29/09/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Minister of State Administration and Local Self-government Zoran Loncar announced on Friday (29 September) that the main political parties have agreed on a proposal for the new constitution.
In a statement to the state TV RTS, Loncar praised the constructive approach displayed by all parties.
According to local media reports, a referendum on the constitution could be held in early November.
(RTS, Tanjug, Beta, Blic - 29/09/06)
